<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1573] IndexWriter does not do the right thing when a Thread is interrupt()&apos;d</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1573</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Spinoff from here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Deadlock-with-concurrent-merges-and-IndexWriter--Lucene-2.4--to22714290.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Deadlock-with-concurrent-merges-and-IndexWriter--Lucene-2.4--to22714290.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When a Thread is interrupt()&apos;d while inside Lucene, there is a risk currently that it will cause a spinloop and starve BG merges from completing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, when possible, we should allow interruption.  But unfortunately for back-compat, we will need to wrap the exception in an unchecked version.  In 3.0 we can change that to simply throw InterruptedException.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
